    <!--
    ========================================================================
    PUÑUY APU - SLEEP TRACKER APPLICATION STRINGS
    PHASE 1: FOUNDATION & CORE STRUCTURE
    ========================================================================

    IMPORTANT NOTES FOR TRANSLATORS:

    1. APP CONTEXT: This is a sleep tracking app that passively monitors when users
       go to sleep and wake up by detecting phone usage patterns. "Puñuy Apu"
       means "Sleep Mountain" in Quechua (indigenous language of the Andes).

    2. TONE GUIDELINES:
       - Warm, encouraging, and supportive throughout
       - Never judgmental about sleep habits
       - Health-focused but not medical/clinical
       - Personal and friendly, like a caring friend

    3. TECHNICAL TERMS: Explain complex concepts in simple language. Users should
       understand features without technical background.

    4. PLACEHOLDERS:
       - %s = string replacement (times, text)
       - %d = number replacement (counts, durations)
       - %1$s, %2$s = multiple ordered replacements
       DO NOT TRANSLATE THESE MARKERS

    5. CULTURAL ADAPTATION: Sleep habits vary by culture. Adapt language to be
       appropriate for local context while keeping core meaning.

    6. CHARACTER LIMITS:
       - Button text: Keep under 20 characters when possible
       - Notification text: Under 50 characters for titles
       - Error messages: Clear and concise
    ========================================================================
    -->

